headline: Why Super Micro Computer Stock Was Sliding This Week
summary: Shares of Super Micro Computer (NASDAQ: SMCI) were heading lower this week as a combination of a sell rating from Goldman Sachs and a broader sell-off in artificial intelligence (AI) stock, which weighed on the maker of AI servers.  According to data from S&P Global Market Intelligence, the stock was down 16.5% for the week as of 3:12 p.m. ET on Thursday.  Is Super Micro Computer in trouble?
